body: @david-macleod : Alas, "The DirectML execution provider currently supports ONNX opset 12" ([doc](https://onnxruntime.ai/docs/execution-providers/DirectML-ExecutionProvider.html#support-coverage)), and your model is opset 13. We have pending work to update the DML EP to 15, but for now, does opset 12 work for you?
Thanks! I have tried opset 12 and it works for my most of my current use cases, is there any timescale for when support for 15 might be available?

@david-macleod Glad to hear it works for most. Opset 15 wouldn't be until after Christmas. There's at least a month of work, and many of us are disappearing during chunks of December for winter vacation. ‚ùÑüìÜ
Ok great, thanks for the heads-up!

Has there been any movement on this?

I notice that some ops appear to have opset 13 listed as supported, but this doesn't seem to be a recent addition
https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/blob/6db6ee5710be7d247e7eace007dbfca1917a4cf8/onnxruntime/core/providers/dml/DmlExecutionProvider/src/Operators/OperatorRegistration.cpp#L634

@david-macleod : Yeah, I added a number of operators to opset 13 (see below from Nov and Feb), but not the complete opset which needs DML API updates. Hence our documentation still states opset 12, because claiming support for opset 13 would be misleading as those ops would still fall back to the CPU (which can yield bad perf due to GPU<->CPU stalls). The remaining opset support will be out by ORT 1.12.

Hi @fdwr - would this explain the errors that I'm seeing trying to run an ONNX model w/ opset 15 and a Div node (w/ DML EP)?

```
Error running model inference: Non-zero status code returned while running Div node. Name:'Div_3' Status Message: D:\a\_work\1\s\include\onnxruntime\core/common/logging/logging.h:289 onnxruntime::logging::LoggingManager::DefaultLogger Attempt to use DefaultLogger but none has been registered.
```

@carsonswope What ORT version? 1.12 in current master?

Your model should get CPU fallback for [Div opset 14](https://github.com/onnx/onnx/blob/main/docs/Operators.md#Div) (there is no Div-15, meaning it resolves to Div-14) in absence of a higher priority EP registration. The error message is perplexing because the DML EP barely uses the logger, and certainly not the DML EP's elementwise division kernel. Do you get the same error running just CPU?
@david-macleod The ORT 1.12 release is imminent, supporting 13-15.

@carsonswope 
> works as expected with the 1.12 release candidate

Glad to hear.

>Thanks for the example code of how to use DirectML w/ ORT by the way

Welcome. Note it's not an *official* blessed sample (I believe @martinb35 has work lined up to create a sample for the official repo, calling ORT with D3D tensors), but I just needed something *myself* to debug it too üòã.
